task.action:
In all three transaction hooks, add `.filter(([, data]) => data !== undefined)`
to every `getQueriesData` call inside `onMutate` handlers.

1. `src/hooks/useExpenseTransactionsQuery.ts`:
   - In `createExpenseTransactionMutation.onMutate`: add filter after `getQueriesData`
   - In `deleteExpenseTransactionMutation.onMutate`: add filter after `getQueriesData`

2. `src/hooks/useIncomeTransactionsQuery.ts`:
   - In `createIncomeTransactionMutation.onMutate`: add filter after `getQueriesData`
   - In `deleteIncomeTransactionMutation.onMutate`: add filter after `getQueriesData`

3. `src/hooks/useTransferTransactionsQuery.ts`:
   - In `createTransferMutation.onMutate`: add filter after `getQueriesData`
   - In `deleteTransferMutation.onMutate`: add filter after `getQueriesData`

The change is the same in all 6 locations:
```
// Before:
const previousTransactions = queryClient.getQueriesData<XxxResponse>({
  queryKey: QUERY_KEYS.xxxTransactions,
});

// After:
const previousTransactions = queryClient.getQueriesData<XxxResponse>({
  queryKey: QUERY_KEYS.xxxTransactions,
}).filter(([, data]) => data !== undefined);
```

This prevents `undefined` cache entries (created by bare hook calls in edit
drawers) from being included in the rollback snapshot, which would wipe real
cache data on `onError` rollback.
